		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Also I just noticed that some earlier MMC1 Koei games use the MMC5 case but have "Nintendo" in place of "FAMICOM" and additionally some of the later MMC1 games use the "FAMICOM" like MMC5 so this isn't a perfect way to detect MMC5.</div>
<br />
<br />And this game <a href="http://bootgod.dyndns.org:7777/profile.php?id=1531" class="postlink">http://bootgod.dyndns.org:7777/profile.php?id=1531</a>   comes in a big purple famicom case but it is a MMC1.  So I think it's better to know the cart before buying it.  I bought this one out of the current theory but it failed <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> But that's ok, at the price I paid and since I didn't have it, I don't mind much.  
<br />
<br />Now, after reading back the specs, it's a MMC1 with CHR-RAM. hmmmm.. Maybe this cart is useful after all.  How useful is an MMC1 + VRAM?

		

