		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">kyuusaku wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">[SUROM] will give you access to 512K of PRG ROM, but only through convoluted bankswitching</div><br />A typical game of that size has at least two screens that use nearly disjoint engines. Viewed in that light, a mapper designed for a dual-SNROM multicart isn't so convoluted.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"> so it's probably not in any way preferrable to MMC3 unless you need one-screen mirroring.</div>
<br />Or unless you plan to mass-produce. MMC3 hasn't yet been made to fit on a CPLD.

		

