	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />A lot of people collect games just as much for the hardware as the software (I have a prototype Famicom cart that I would never part with, even though I've dumped the ROM). There is a finite supply of original NES/Fami hardware; just because something is plentiful right now doesn't mean it'll be plentiful 10 years or so down the road. Parts wear out, game shops trash their bins of old games, supply gradually dwindles. Butchering carts only serves to accelerate the process.
<br />
<br />It'd be great if the PowerPak was cheaper, more readily available, and had better mapper support... <img src="./images/smilies/icon_sad.gif" alt=":(" title="Sad" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


